\title{Nbt}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Use the nbt! macro from mc_protocol for creating NBT (Named Binary Tag) data for Minecraft protocol encoding.}

\subtree{
\title{NBT Encoding Skill}
\p{Use the \code{\startverb nbt!\stopverb} macro from \code{\startverb mc_protocol\stopverb} for creating NBT data.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\p{Use this skill when you need to:}

\ul{
\li{Encode NBT data for Minecraft packets}
\li{Create text components for chat, action bar, titles}
\li{Build compound NBT structures}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Basic Usage}
\pre{\startverb
use mc_protocol::nbt;

// Simple compound
let compound = nbt! {
    "text" => "Hello",
    "count" => 42i32,
    "flag" => true,
};

// Convert to network bytes
let bytes = compound.to_network_bytes();
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Nested Compounds}
\pre{\startverb
use mc_protocol::nbt;

let nested = nbt! {
    "outer" => nbt! {
        "inner" => 123i32,
    },
};
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Supported Types}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb i8\stopverb} - Byte}
\li{\code{\startverb i16\stopverb} - Short}
\li{\code{\startverb i32\stopverb} - Int}
\li{\code{\startverb i64\stopverb} - Long}
\li{\code{\startverb f32\stopverb} - Float}
\li{\code{\startverb f64\stopverb} - Double}
\li{\code{\startverb &str\stopverb} / \code{\startverb String\stopverb} - String}
\li{\code{\startverb bool\stopverb} - Byte (0 or 1)}
\li{\code{\startverb NbtCompound\stopverb} - Nested compound}
\li{\code{\startverb NbtList\stopverb} - List of same-type elements}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Text Components (Chat/Action Bar)}
\p{For Minecraft text components (used in chat, action bar, titles):}

\pre{\startverb
use mc_protocol::nbt;

// Simple text
let text_component = nbt! {
    "text" => "Hello World",
};

// With color
let colored = nbt! {
    "text" => "Red text",
    "color" => "red",
};
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Always use the \code{\startverb nbt!\stopverb} macro} instead of manual byte manipulation}
\li{Use explicit type suffixes (\code{\startverb 42i32\stopverb}, \code{\startverb 1.0f32\stopverb}) for numeric literals}
\li{Use \code{\startverb to_network_bytes()\stopverb} for protocol encoding (adds type tag, no root name)}
}
}
}